{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":12861,"name":"","username":"szamq","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/szamq/{size}/66_2.png","created_at":"2016-07-17T12:55:21.000Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eI‚Äôm working on OpenVR. The one way communication is done - I can get rotation and position of person wearing the oculus.\u003cbr\u003e\nNow is time to send the visuals to the hmd. I already have the stereo rendering implemented, but it goes on the screen/ monitor like here \u003ca href=\"http://www.gnometech.com/torque/images/blog-2013-04-11/2013-04-11-StereoRendering.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003egnometech.com/torque/images/ ‚Ä¶ dering.jpg\u003c/a\u003e\u003cbr\u003e\nWhat I wold like to do is to copy the screen as a texture, so I could send it to the vr googles.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI tried to do it like that. But it is upside down and It stops to render on screen\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode\u003e        renderTexture = Texture2D();\n        renderTexture.SetSize(1920, 1080, GetRGBFormat(), TEXTURE_RENDERTARGET);\n        renderTexture.filterMode = FILTER_BILINEAR;\n\n        RenderSurface@ surface = renderTexture.renderSurface;\n    surface.updateMode=SURFACE_UPDATEALWAYS;\n        surface.viewports[0] = renderer.viewports[0];\n    surface.viewports[1] = renderer.viewports[1];\n\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there a better way to grab, what‚Äôs on screen and have that as a texture(that is accesible by glBindTexture‚Ä¶)?\u003cbr\u003e\nedit:\u003cbr\u003e\nOk just noticed that the upside down view of the texture is not caused by urho but by OpenVR, I‚Äôm wondering why\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-01-02T01:13:17.494Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":45,"reads":12,"readers_count":11,"score":242.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":2124,"topic_slug":"grab-screen-texture","display_username":"","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_ur